properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued February 11 at 3:32PM CST until February 12 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Sioux Falls SD
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blizzard conditions expected. Total snow accumulations of
up to one inch. Winds gusting as high as 45 mph and wind chills
as low as 35 below.

* WHERE...Portions of east central South Dakota and southwest
Minnesota.

* WHEN...From 9 AM to 6 PM CST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute. The dangerously
cold wind chills as low as 35 below zero could cause frostbite
on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Travel should be restricted to emergencies only. If you must
travel, have a winter survival kit with you. If you get stranded,
stay with your vehicle.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: BLIZZARD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM TO 6 PM CST WEDNESDAY
